First clue: The shape of my face is often thought to help tell how long I will live. Longer face = longer life.
Sweet treats for humans such as grapes and chocolate, can cause me kidney failure.
I am thought to have a great internal clock and can tell what time of day it is.
I have a distinct nose print pattern that can be used to identify me like a human fingerprint.
Showing your teeth to me can be seen as a sign of aggression, even if it is just a friendly smile.